[[Image:NI Slieve Binnian.jpg|250px|right|thumb|Slieve Binnian (''{{lang|ga|Sliabh Binneáin}}'') in the Mourne Mountains]]
[[Hewitt (hill)|Hewitts]] are hills in England, Wales and [[Ireland]] that are at least {{convert|2000|ft|m}} high with a relative height of at least {{convert|30|m|abbr=on}}. The original list, covering only England and Wales, was compiled by Alan Dawson and originally published in ''The Relative Hills of Britain'' under the name ''Sweats''.<ref name="rhb">{{cite book | last=Dawson | first=Alan | year=1992 | title=The Relative Hills of Britain | url=http://bubl.ac.uk/org/tacit/marilyns/ | publisher=Cicerone Press | location=Milnthorpe | id=ISBN 1-85284-068-4}}</ref> The list was subsequently renamed ''Hewitts'' to include Ireland, updated, and published in a series of three booklets edited by Dave Hewitt: ''The Hewitts and Marilyns of Wales'',<ref>{{cite book | title=The Hewitts and Marilyns of Wales | last=Dawson | first=Alan | url=http://bubl.ac.uk/org/tacit/tables/wales/ | id=ISBN 0-9522680-6-X | publisher=TACit Press | location=Cambuskenneth, Stirling | year=1997}}</ref> ''The Hewitts and Marilyns of England''<ref>{{cite book | title=The Hewitts and Marilyns of England | last=Dawson | first=Alan | url=http://bubl.ac.uk/org/tacit/tables/england/ | id=ISBN 0-9522680-7-8 | publisher=TACit Press | location=Cambuskenneth, Stirling | year=1997}}</ref> and ''The Hewitts and Marilyns of Ireland''.<ref>{{cite book | title=The Hewitts and Marilyns of Ireland | last=Clements | first=E. D. | url=http://bubl.ac.uk/org/tacit/tables/ireland.html | id=ISBN 0-9522680-8-6 | publisher=TACit Press | location=Cambuskenneth, Stirling | year=1997}}</ref>

There are 211 Hewitts in [[Ireland]], 19 of which lie in [[Northern Ireland]]:

Region 43 (Armagh, Down, Antrim)
* [[Slieve Donard]] – {{convert|850|m|abbr=on}}
* [[Chimney Rock Mountain]] – {{convert|656|m|abbr=on}}
* [[Slieve Commedagh]] – {{convert|767|m|abbr=on}}
* [[Slieve Binnian]] – {{convert|747|m|abbr=on}}
* Slieve Binnian North Top – {{convert|678|m|abbr=on}}
* [[Slieve Bearnagh]] – {{convert|739|m|abbr=on}}
* [[Slieve Meelbeg]] – {{convert|708|m|abbr=on}}
* [[Slieve Meelmore]] – {{convert|704|m|abbr=on}}
* [[Slieve Loughshannagh]] – {{convert|620|m|abbr=on}}
* [[Slievelamagan]] – {{convert|704|m|abbr=on}}
* [[Cove Mountain]] – {{convert|655|m|abbr=on}}
* [[Slieve Muck]] – {{convert|673|m|abbr=on}}
* [[Eagle Mountain (Mourne)|Eagle Mountain]] – {{convert|638|m|abbr=on}}
* [[Shanlieve]] – {{convert|627|m|abbr=on}}

Region 44 (Londonderry, Tyrone, Fermanagh) 
* [[Sawel Mountain]] – {{convert|678|m|abbr=on}}
* [[Dart Mountain]] – {{convert|619|m|abbr=on}}
* [[Mullaghclogha]] – {{convert|635|m|abbr=on}}
* [[Mullaghaneany]] – {{convert|627|m|abbr=on}}
* [[Meenard Mountain]] – {{convert|625|m|abbr=on}}

One further Hewitt lies on the border, and is the highest point of two counties [[Cavan]] and [[Fermanagh]] and of the border itself:

Region 45 (Donegal to Sligo)
* [[Cuilcagh]] – {{convert|665|m|abbr=on}}

